he start date and the end date <= 1500`\n\n- `1 <= step <= 1000`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/date-range-generator/","problemName":"Date Range Generator","problemNumber":2777,"problemSlug":"date-range-generator","schemaVersion":2,"sequenceIndex":2777,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["Array","Enumeration"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **1-indexed** integer array `nums` of length `n`.\n\nAn element `nums[i]` of `nums` is called **special** if `i` divides `n`, i.e. `n % i == 0`.\n\nReturn *the **sum of the squares** of all **special** elements of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [1,2,3,4]\nOutput: 21\nExplanation: There are exactly 3 special elements in nums: nums[1] since 1 divides 4, nums[2] since 2 divides 4, and nums[4] since 4 divides 4. \nHence, the sum of the squares of all special elements of nums is nums[1] * nums[1] + nums[2] * nums[2] + nums[4] * nums[4] = 1 * 1 + 2 * 2 + 4 * 4 = 21.  ","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [2,7,1,19,18,3]\nOutput: 63\nExplanation: There are exactly 4 special elements in nums: nums[1] since 1 divides 6, nums[2] since 2 divides 6, nums[3] since 3 divides 6, and nums[6] since 6 divides 6. \nHence, the sum of the squares of all special elements of nums is nums[1] * nums[1] + nums[2] * nums[2] + nums[3] * nums[3] + nums[6] * nums[6] = 2 * 2 + 7 * 7 + 1 * 1 + 3 * 3 = 63. ","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length == n <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 50`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["Array","Enumeration"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"You are given a **1-indexed** integer array `nums` of length `n`.\n\nAn element `nums[i]` of `nums` is called **special** if `i` divides `n`, i.e. `n % i == 0`.\n\nReturn *the **sum of the squares** of all **special** elements of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: nums = [1,2,3,4]\nOutput: 21\nExplanation: There are exactly 3 special elements in nums: nums[1] since 1 divides 4, nums[2] since 2 divides 4, and nums[4] since 4 divides 4. \nHence, the sum of the squares of all special elements of nums is nums[1] * nums[1] + nums[2] * nums[2] + nums[4] * nums[4] = 1 * 1 + 2 * 2 + 4 * 4 = 21.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: nums = [2,7,1,19,18,3]\nOutput: 63\nExplanation: There are exactly 4 special elements in nums: nums[1] since 1 divides 6, nums[2] since 2 divides 6, nums[3] since 3 divides 6, and nums[6] since 6 divides 6. \nHence, the sum of the squares of all special elements of nums is nums[1] * nums[1] + nums[2] * nums[2] + nums[3] * nums[3] + nums[6] * nums[6] = 2 * 2 + 7 * 7 + 1 * 1 + 3 * 3 = 63.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `1 <= nums.length == n <= 50`\n\n- `1 <= nums[i] <= 50`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/sum-of-squares-of-special-elements/","problemName":"Sum of Squares of Special Elements","problemNumber":2778,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"You are given a **1-indexed** integer array `nums` of length `n`.\n\nAn element `nums[i]` of `nums` is called **special** if `i` divides `n`, i.e. `n % i == 0`.\n\nReturn *the **sum of the squares** of all **special** elements of *`nums`.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: nums = [1,2,3,4]\nOutput: 21\nExplanation: There are exactly 3 special elements in nums: nums[1] since 1 divides 4, nums[2] since 2 divides 4, and nums[4] since 4 divides 4. \nHence, the sum of the squares of all special elements of nums is nums[1] * nums[1] + nums[2] * nums[2] + nums[4] * nums[4] = 1 * 1 + 2 * 2 + 4 * 4 = 21.  ","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: nums = [2,7,1,1