ex":2793,"solutionApproaches":[]},{"assets":[],"categories":["JavaScript"],"constraintBlocks":[],"contentBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given two arrays `keysArr` and `valuesArr`, return a new object `obj`. Each key-value pair in `obj` should come from `keysArr[i]` and `valuesArr[i]`.\n\nIf a duplicate key exists at a previous index, that key-value should be excluded. In other words, only the first key should be added to the object.\n\nIf the key is not a string, it should be converted into a string by calling `String()` on it.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: keysArr = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"], valuesArr = [1, 2, 3]\nOutput: {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2, \"c\": 3}\nExplanation: The keys \"a\", \"b\", and \"c\" are paired with the values 1, 2, and 3 respectively.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: keysArr = [\"1\", 1, false], valuesArr = [4, 5, 6]\nOutput: {\"1\": 4, \"false\": 6}\nExplanation: First, all the elements in keysArr are converted into strings. We can see there are two occurrences of \"1\". The value associated with the first occurrence of \"1\" is used: 4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: keysArr = [], valuesArr = []\nOutput: {}\nExplanation: There are no keys so an empty object is returned.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `keysArr` and `valuesArr` are valid JSON arrays\n\n- `2 <= JSON.stringify(keysArr).length, JSON.stringify(valuesArr).length <= 5 * 10⁵`\n\n- `keysArr.length === valuesArr.length`","type":"text"}],"contentHtml":"","contentHtmlLocal":"","databaseEntry":{"categories":["JavaScript"],"createdAt":0,"difficulty":"Easy","lastRevisionAt":0,"problem":"Given two arrays `keysArr` and `valuesArr`, return a new object `obj`. Each key-value pair in `obj` should come from `keysArr[i]` and `valuesArr[i]`.\n\nIf a duplicate key exists at a previous index, that key-value should be excluded. In other words, only the first key should be added to the object.\n\nIf the key is not a string, it should be converted into a string by calling `String()` on it.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"], valuesArr = [1, 2, 3]\nOutput: {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2, \"c\": 3}\nExplanation: The keys \"a\", \"b\", and \"c\" are paired with the values 1, 2, and 3 respectively.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [\"1\", 1, false], valuesArr = [4, 5, 6]\nOutput: {\"1\": 4, \"false\": 6}\nExplanation: First, all the elements in keysArr are converted into strings. We can see there are two occurrences of \"1\". The value associated with the first occurrence of \"1\" is used: 4.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [], valuesArr = []\nOutput: {}\nExplanation: There are no keys so an empty object is returned.\n\n**Constraints:**\n\n- `keysArr` and `valuesArr` are valid JSON arrays\n\n- `2 <= JSON.stringify(keysArr).length, JSON.stringify(valuesArr).length <= 5 * 10⁵`\n\n- `keysArr.length === valuesArr.length`","problemLink":"https://leetcode.com/problems/create-object-from-two-arrays/","problemName":"Create Object from Two Arrays","problemNumber":2794,"revisionAnchorAt":0,"revisionCount":0,"revisionDates":[],"revisionPlanHours":[1,24,168,336,672],"solutionCode":"","testCases":"","updatedAt":0},"descriptionBlocks":[{"sequence":0,"text":"Given two arrays `keysArr` and `valuesArr`, return a new object `obj`. Each key-value pair in `obj` should come from `keysArr[i]` and `valuesArr[i]`.\n\nIf a duplicate key exists at a previous index, that key-value should be excluded. In other words, only the first key should be added to the object.\n\nIf the key is not a string, it should be converted into a string by calling `String()` on it.\n\n**Example 1:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":1,"text":"Input: keysArr = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"], valuesArr = [1, 2, 3]\nOutput: {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2, \"c\": 3}\nExplanation: The keys \"a\", \"b\", and \"c\" are paired with the values 1, 2, and 3 respectively.","type":"code"},{"sequence":2,"text":"**Example 2:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":3,"text":"Input: keysArr = [\"1\", 1, false], valuesArr = [4, 5, 6]\nOutput: {\"1\": 4, \"false\": 6}\nExplanation: First, all the elements in keysArr are converted into strings. We can see there are two occurrences of \"1\". The value associated with the first occurrence of \"1\" is used: 4.","type":"code"},{"sequence":4,"text":"**Example 3:**","type":"text"},{"sequence":5,"text":"Input: keysArr = [], valuesArr = []\nOutput: {}\nExplanation: There are no keys so an empty object is returned.","type":"code"},{"sequence":6,"text":"**Constraints:**\n\n- `keysArr` and `valuesArr` are valid JSON arrays\n\n- `2 <= JSON.stringify(keysArr).length, JSON.stringify(valuesArr).length <= 5 * 10⁵`\n\n- `keysArr.length === valuesArr.length`","type":"text"}],"difficulty":"Easy","examples":[],"paidOnly":false,"problem":"Given two arrays `keysArr` and `valuesArr`, return a new object `obj`. Each key-value pair in `obj` should come from `keysArr[i]` and `valuesArr[i]`.\n\nIf a duplicate key exists at a previous index, that key-value should be excluded. In other words, only the first key should be added to the object.\n\nIf the key is not a string, it should be converted into a string by calling `String()` on it.\n\n**Example 1:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [\"a\", \"b\", \"c\"], valuesArr = [1, 2, 3]\nOutput: {\"a\": 1, \"b\": 2, \"c\": 3}\nExplanation: The keys \"a\", \"b\", and \"c\" are paired with the values 1, 2, and 3 respectively.\n\n**Example 2:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [\"1\", 1, false], valuesArr = [4, 5, 6]\nOutput: {\"1\": 4, \"false\": 6}\nExplanation: First, all the elements in keysArr are converted into strings. We can see there are two occurrences of \"1\". The value associated with the first occurrence of \"1\" is used: 4.\n\n**Example 3:**\n\nInput: keysArr = [], valuesArr = []\nOutput: {}\nExplanation: There are no keys so an empty object is returned.\n\n**Constraints:**